The paper discusses optimization algorithms and their convergence properties, which are typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories of arXiv CS. The use of probability distributions and natural gradients also suggests a connection to probabilistic methods in machine learning and optimization, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
